$ Shell command: lsb_release
@ lsb_release

`lsb_release` can be used to determine the version of a Linux distribution: `lsb_release -a | grep release`.

`lsb` stands for → Linux/LSB[Linux Standard Base].

{ Identify a distribution #identify-distribution

  A → Linux/distributions[Linux distribution] is generally identifiable with
code {
lsb_release -d
code }


Specific numbered relases are identified by
code {
lsb_release -r
code }

}

